brought up if not asked. We did call down about the TV. Basically, when you
turn it on it has static and doesn't work when you use the channel button

came up to help, she told us to just key in the channel we wanted to watch
and that worked. So, the questionnaire asked if anything didn't work as
expected and that was the TV in the bedroom part of the room.

Melanie

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Cleaning staff should take more care to ensure that bedding is actually clean. The front desk staff were all veryfriendly, but the wait staff in the restaurant and breakfast buffet were some of the rudest people I made contact with in Greenbay.

column65:
In town for the Packer game.  Staff was very helpful with Packer game shuttle information at check-in.  Even though due to our travel plans we arrived before the standard check-in time, Kolton checked, our room was ready and we were able to check in early. 
After a long flight and a car ride, it was so nice to be able to drop off our bags and freshen up a bit before we went to our stadium tour.   I have many times stayed places where the staff doesn't even check if the room is ready and just repeats the check-in time and says OK when I ask if there is a way we can store our bags, so this was very noticed and appreciated. 
The room was spacious and  everything was clean and as expected.  This was a perfect stay for our Packer game girls weekend.

Also, the price of the room was $99 when we booked the room but went up to $299 because the Packers had a home game that weekend. Ridiculous!! column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;We had a completely awful experience at this hotel. Our room was not cleaned after been gone for 9 hours. Then, when we ordered room service, they brought the wrong ice cream and no silverware (no big deal) when we called down they were so rude and said it would be a long wait. Then, after the correct ice cream was brought up, the girl asked to see the other ice cream because she thought we were lying. After this, a security guard pounded on our door and threatened to kick us out of the hotel because we “threw ice cream at the girl”. We were shocked and felt so threatened and uncomfortable. This was a completely made up story, and when we expressed this, the security guard and waitress stormed away saying that our opinion was irrelevant and that if we left our room again we would be kicked out of the hotel.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

2019-12-19 08:13:19] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Ms. Likens,

I sincerely apologize for the experience you had while staying with us at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay. I'm finding it difficult to convey through an email how horrified I am by the treatment you received from our colleagues.

I have already spoken with our Head of Security and Food & Beverage Manager regarding your experience. After putting some of the puzzle pieces together, I feel that there was misinterpretation and miscommunication surrounding the situation and our staff acted completely out of line. We are working with the colleagues that were involved and will be coaching them on better ways to asses a situation with guests and certainly handle situations better. Much to my frustration, a situation was created over ice cream - I can imagine how frustrated you that this situation got to the level it did.

I would also like to apologize that housekeeping did not clean your room while you were out of the room for 9 hours. I have spoken with our Executive Housekeeper so that she can work with her team to see where the ball was dropped. 

As a goodwill gesture, I have already credited back 1-night's room and tax. You will see $432.42 refunded back to your VISA in 7-10 business days if you view your account online. 

Again, I sincerely apologize for the inconveniences you experienced while staying with us. I want to assure you, we are coaching our team so that this never happens again. If you wish you discuss anything further with me, please do not hesitate to reach out - I will be glad to speak with you.

I wish you an your family the happiest of holidays.

Warm regards,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager

Thank you for taking the time to fill out our guest satisfaction survey, and thank you for being a World of Hyatt member. We do appreciate your continued loyalty to Hyatt. 

We are sorry to hear your stay did not go as well as expected. We strive to provide the best guest experience, and we are sorry we fell short. We will discuss with our team to ensure there is follow through with our front desk team for housekeeping requests, and ensuring they are completed. We are also sorry about the cleanliness of the ottoman, I will pass along the feedback to our housekeeping team. As for parking, we do charge $7 nightly for parking. As a one time courtesy, I have credited back the $7 charge, but do know in the future, you will have the parking charged to your room. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;We were there for 2 days prior to a game day.  The breakfast staff knew they were going to be extra busy at breakfast on game day but failed miserably in service and food replenishment.  I could not see someone keeping on track on the food and letting the kitchen staff know of low supply.  I waited for 10 minutes for replenishment of the bagels/toast, I asked someone who said they would sort out, it was not replenished by the time I left.  I had to ask someone for coffee.  When I mentioned it upon check out that my husband and I didn't have much to eat (as could not continue to wait), there was no acknowledgement by the wait staff or letting the guests know how long they would likely have to wait. The staff at the reception were very accommodating and provided me with  money to spend at the cafe as my room rate also included breakfast.  They also discounted the car parking rate, so this was satisfactory to me, although next time I will not include any breakfast.  I have stayed at the hotel on past occasion and was happy that is why we returned even though the rate was extremely high compared to other accoms in the area.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column66: The front desk was nice but our interactions in the restaurant were AWFUL. See below.
column67: The room was nice, but was so hot!! We had the unit turned all the way down but it was still very hot.
column68:
We ate at the sports bar on Friday. When we went in, a girl seated us and asked about drinks. We asked if you had Prosecco. She disappeared and never returned. We also asked if she could put the Wisconsin game on the two TVs we were facing and she never returned. We went to the bar and the man there would not help us either. We then had another server come over and it felt like it was his first night ever working. It took 3 times to get us water. We ordered prosecco and what we got was definitely not prosecco.  He later came back and said it's only served by the bottle so they weren't going to charge us. I'm not sure what wine it was, but it was old. We finally ordered but that was a challenge too. We asked if the chicken wings were breaded and if there were other types of cheese but he did not know and had to go check and took forever to come back. We finally got our food 45 minutes later (was not busy). They never checked on us until much later when we finally ordered a bottle of wine. We were very nice the whole time and not sure why were treated so poorly.

On saturday, we came in after the Packers game and went straight to the bar. We were not greeted in a nice way but we did ask to order a bottle of wine to go and some chicken wings. The first bottle of wine she brought wasn't even the right one (my friend is allergic to California wines) and when we told her she didn't apologize or anything and just rudely walked away and got the new bottle, opened it up away from us and then brought it back. A server finally brought our wings to go but the bartender never thanked us or said anything more.

Overall, the dining experience was really bad which is disappointing b/c I stay in Hyatts all over the country all the time and have never had this bad of an experience.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I was travelling and needed an unexpected stop in Green Bay to break the drive.  I used the App to find a Hyatt, check its pet and parking policy (as I had both a car and a dog) and then paid for my room 20 minutes before I arrived at the hotel.  On check in I was told the pet fee is $100 per night.  There is nothing on the app on pet fees, but is on parking.  When I asked the manager I could either cancel and loose the payment on the room due to being inside the wrong time frame or pay the money.  I asked for confirmation on where on the App it talks about pet fees and they could only provide me information from the web.  I should not have to check the web for this information, not when it is so clearly written in the app on the car parking charges.  $100 is too steep - my dog went from his carry bag into his crate without touching the carpet or furniture.  No deep clean was needed, and how much deep cleaning is done for $100 anyway.  Kids that were running wild in the hotel would have used more time of your cleaning staff than my dog, but they stay for free.  Seriously bad customer service by Hyatt not to declare the fee on the App when advertising you are pet friendly and then to have the staff be so unhelpful in explaining it when raised.  Very disappointed.; ;You can see from my comments it was not a great stay and seriously has me in doubt about using Hyatt again.  I value honesty and if Hyatt is not going to be upfront about fees on its App, then I really don't trust the brand.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

2019-12-07 14:15:29] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Ms. Christopherson, 

Thank you for your honest feedback in our survey. I sincerely apologize that your stay with us was more frustrating than it was relaxing and comfortable on your drive.

I logged into my World of Hyatt app and I could see what you're referring to. I spoke with my contact from our Global Technology Team and pet fees and other hotel fees are not listed on the app aside from parking. Parking and Transportation takes you to a different page in the app where they can post information about both options. Hyatt Hotels that are pet friendly list it as an amenity and that list can vary from hotel to hotel and does not take you to a separate page - it's just a list of amenities. I checked 6 properties around the United States that are pet friendly and none have their fees listed in the app. Our website, as well as other properties sites, do make the hotel fees available to you - that's on the website though, not the app. I have shared your feedback with the Global Technology Team to see if that is an update that can take place in the future on the app. 

In regards to the interactions you had with the front desk staff, I will be speaking with all of them individually in regards to your concerns. I will personally be working with my staff to ensure they know the proper way to assist guests in situations where there is a conflict of information.Your concerns could have been handled better; however, the policy of the Hyatt Regency Green Bay covers all guests with pets and you were provided with our policy, regardless of where it was posted. Pet cleanings are handled by housekeeping differently and do take more time upon check out. The policy is applied equally to all guests with a pet. There was no malicious intent by Hyatt Hotels to hide information and I sincerely apologize that you feel that way. If you do choose to stay with Hyatt Hotels in the future, please reach out to the hotel directly to ask about their pet fees. I would highly recommend checking with all hotel brands as well as many do charge pet cleaning fees. 

As a goodwill gesture for the confusion and inconvenience, I have gone ahead and waived the pet fee for you. You should see the refund posted in your account in 7-10 business days. 

If there is anything else you wish to discuss, please do not hesitate to reach out. 

Warm regards and have a happy holiday season,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay

column77: I had to stop to break up a long drive, so using the App I looked at Green Bay Hyatt for a stop.  Very clearly the App states that the hotel is pet-friendly, and that parking is avaialble for $7 per night.  I read all the terms and policies of the App for the pet fee and could find nothing.  Great, I booked in and arrived 20 minutes later.  On arrival I was told that $100 pet fee applied for my chihuahua and no explanation could be given why this is not stated on the App.  I had the choice to cancel the booking and forfeit the room payment, or pay the $100.  I would loose $100 bucks either way, so I stayed.  I did complain and speak to management.  They were unhelpful and could only find the pet fee on their full website, which defeats the purpose of having an App for ease of booking.  My chihuahua went from dog transport container to travel crate without ever touching the ground.  Hope the $100 deep clean fee I paid meant the person after me enjoy the extra work the staff had to do on my departure!!

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I always check for bedbugs at any hotel, even 5-star. In doing so I always notice whether anyone cleans in the corners, under the beds, behind headboards, etc. You may want to do an annual deep-clean on the rooms, because it looks like no one has cleaned those areas for years (or ever). It's not a big deal, but if those areas aren't being cleaned, then bedbugs could technically hide there and never be found.; ;I am a member, but it wasn't mentioned.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Thank you for taking our Guest Satisfaction Survey. I sincerely apologize that we did not meet your expectations during your stay.

I would like an opportunity to know what I can do to assist you. When we saw your reservation in our pre-arrival report and read the reviews you left on Google and Facebook, we wanted to make sure we did everything in our power to make your stay comfortable and relaxing. We attempted to reach out to you twice. I was advised by our Director of Sales, Tracy and our Reservations Manager, Carrie that they both attempted to reach out to you and their request to assist you were not responded to. 

Prior to your arrival, we blocked your room so that no other guests were in the room the night before. Our Executive Housekeeper and one of our senior housekeepers personally attended to your room to ensure the room was prepared for your arrival. The day of your arrival, our Executive Housekeeper then inspected the room again to ensure nothing changed prior to your arriving. Your room was handled with the utmost care so that your experience was better than before. No one had access to your room aside from you and our Executive Housekeeper. 

I personally checked you out of your room on the morning of departure. You did not bring any of your concerns to my attention. Also, our attempts at reaching out have been going unanswered. As discussed in previous communication, you and your father were compensated for your inconveniences from earlier in 2019. 

My question for you is what can I do to assist you? How can we resolve your concerns and your multiple negative reviews? 

Please let me know if there is anything I can do to help. I am available via email and or phone call. 

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay

2019-11-26 19:20:48] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Good evening Ms. Wiersma, 

Thank you for taking the time to fill out our guest satisfaction survey, and thank you for being a World of Hyatt member.  We do appreciate hearing feedback from our guests about their stay. 

We are sorry to hear about the heating issues you experienced during your stay. We strive to provide the best guest experience for our guests during their stay and we are sorry we fell short. With our heating system in our hotel, it is always a struggle to meet everyone preferred temperature as we use an HVAC system.  The HVAC system has two modes, hot and cold mode. With whichever mode is chosen, it is the same mode throughout the hotel.  Depending on the mode, the room is either heated, or cooled, by air being blown over hot water pipes, or cold water pipes. This can cause issues with the rooms not heating up as fast as guests would like. For your stay, we were experience computer issues with some of the rooms and being able to control the temperatures in the room and not being able to heat the rooms properly. Our engineering department works on this daily to try and provide the most comfortable stays for our guests. When the heating system doesn't cooperate, we will use space heaters to help out in trying to keep the guests comfortable. If all else fails, we move a guest to a new room. We do hope the room move was able to provide a better experience for the second part of your stay. 

Due to the heating issues you did have, I have gone ahead and applied 8,000 bonus points onto your World of Hyatt account as compensation. 

We do hope to see you again at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay. 


Sincerely,

Kolton Madlem
Assistant Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay

column65:
When we chose to stay in the Hyatt Regency, we chose it because it had a hot tub.  Unfortunately, when we got into it on Friday, we were disappointed with how cold it was.  We chalked it up to overuse, or poor temperature management.  We were out and about on Saturday, but we decided to take a dip on Sunday before leaving, and it was even COLDER!  I was disappointed in that because that was one of the two requirements we wanted for our rare kid-less weekend get away... 
We were also double-charged for breakfast and I had to call to get a refund.  
The rooms were nice and quiet, and the staff was accommodating, but unfortunately, I don't think that we would be staying there again.
column66: Staff was pleasant at the front desk.  The two young girls at the breakfast buffet were trash talking the Hispanic waiter, so that was disappointing.  They were not very approachable from a guest standpoint to begin with, and then I saw that.  The omelette chef was nice and the woman stocking the buffet was very smiley and seemed happy to be there.

column77: I had purchased a radio shopping show certificate for the Hyatt at a much discounted price.  I'm not sure we could afford to stay at the Hyatt under normal circumstances  The lobby, atrium and rooms were clean and beds were comfortable.  The bathroom was a bit tight quarters and I had to search for the hair dryer which was in the bedroom closet. The suite was nice with a separate area and modular sofa to watch tv along with a bar/counter area with sink  I stayed at this facility at least 40 years ago and had forgotten about the large atrium.  It was very nostalgic.  The breakfast looked good, but we didn't eat as we had made plans to go to a local cafe for breakfast.
column205: Ad previously noted there was an obviously intoxicated and obnoxiously loud male at the bar not far from where we were sitting.  Perhaps should have been cut off before he got to that point.  I was relieved when he and his friends left.

column77: Love the hot-tub and sauna on the cold nights. I have stayed here a few times. The work-out area is large with lots of machines and free-weights. column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;I love the location and the friendliness of the Hyatt Regency Green Bay. But the hotel would benefit from a bit of sprucing up. My room was lovely, but there were places (particularly near the bathroom) where the carpet was pulling up and you could see the floor underneath. The bed had that 'slope' hotel beds get when too many guests have slept on the same side of the bed. It made it a bit frustrating to get comfortable. It would have also been great to have some directions on how to use the thermostat. It took a while for me to figure it out. 

From a "what I liked best" standpoint - aside from the excellent staff - was how quiet the hotel was. I was there on a Packers game weekend (when the Packers won) and was really anticipating a lot of noise, particularly with the big echo-y lobby area. But I barely heard anything. It was great.; ;Hyatt is my preferred brand, whenever I travel.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

2019-11-13 06:29:46] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Mr. Rizzo,

Thank you for sharing your feedback with us.

I sincerely apologize that you were disappointed with your stay and the rates we offered as park of your event. While Green Bay Packer home games can affect room rates throughout the city, we value our weddings guests and their families. Brides and grooms work with our Weddings Team and contract discounted rooms as well as other benefits, too. The bride and groom signed a contract that offered discounts of $160/per night as well as offered complimentary parking, one-night requirements, the option to change/cancel reservations within 48-hours, and available late check-outs. Guests staying with us during game day weekends and NOT part of a wedding group are required to book 2-night minimum stays that are pre-paid and non-refundable reservations. They are also charged for parking and are limited for late check-outs.

As for your concern about the temperature of the room, thank you for bring that to our attention during your stay. I am glad that our team was able to get you moved into a more comfortable room. I will share your feedback with our Leadership Team. 

Please let me know if there is anything else you would like to discuss.

Sincerely,

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;The service in the restaurant was terrible.  The first night, our group was almost the only ones there and it took over 2 hours for us to get food and eat.  It took over 20 minutes to get our checks.  The server seemed overwhelmed, and when some in our party went to the bar for another drink, the bartender told them, "you have a server for that."
The lunch I got the next day was a bit quicker, but still seemed slow.
Dinner the next night was a repeat---very slow.
Food service for the meeting I attended was awkward---plated sandwich and chips, so the chips were soggy from being in the fridge.  No condiments on the tables, so eventually there was a server walking around with boxes of mayo and mustard packets having guests help themselves.  The soup came last, was absolutely tasteless, and was lukewarm.  I would expect better food service to be associated with such a large conference center.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;I had two issues during this stay:
1) Dirty shower. My shower had not been cleaned, as evidenced by multiple pieces of hair (5+) and by the used dry washcloth hanging on the shower rod. I discovered this in the morning when I was in a rush, so I did not have time to request housekeeping service.
2) Parking. There was no space in the hotel lot, so I was directed to parking in the ramp across the street. The front desk informed me that parking would be complimentary in the ramp and that weekend parking was free after 6 pm on Friday. The front desk worker noted that it was about 5 pm but said that should be "fine". When I checked out, I asked the front desk if I needed anything for the ramp parking. I was assured that I did not. When I exited the ramp, my scanned ticket indicated that I owed 85 cents for parking. Certainly a small amount, but definitely a hassle when my purse was not easily within reach and there several cars in line behind me. It was ridiculous to put an 85 cent charge on my credit card.
Both of these things occurring within an hour did not lead to a very good start to my day, especially one in which I had to drive 5 hours.; ;I was pleased that my rewards number was already on my account.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column77: I stayed in a corner king room for a work event.  I requested to receive an email when my room was ready, which was early.  The room was very spacious and comfortable.  They even have motion detected lights under the tables by the bed, so if you get up it lights up (not bright) and you can see your way to the bathroom.  Our event was at the KI Convention Center, which is attached to this hotel.  Overall I would definitely stay here for any other events at KI, or activities in downtown Green Bay.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;The Hyatt was a very welcoming place, from the time I got there until I left.  Staff was eager to assist and always with a smile.  The only problem was when arriving, when coming from the campus direction there isn't a sign that you can see that says Hyatt.  It would be nice to at least have a sign on the side that is facing the road.  Google said I reached my destination, but the only hotel I saw was the one next to the Hyatt. column77: From the time I arrived until I left the staff was very cordial, welcoming, and the hotel was clean. The layout of the hotel was amazing and it made you feel high class.  There wasn't a bad experience during my stay. The pool, sauna, hot tub, and steam room were clean.  The only problem was you can not see the sign to the Hyatt.  Just know if you go under the walkway to the parking ramp on Main St. you are at the Hyatt as it is attached. and there is technically only one way in and you have to turn on Madison St. to get to the entrance.  The exit is on Main St.

2019-10-30 14:16:40] Email received from: Ed Johnson <ejfromwi@gmail.com>: Hello:
Thank you for your interest.  The problem was not with my food, as I had
the fish tacos, and they were fine.  The reubens that two other guests
ordered were not up to any kind of standard.  One person complained that it
was "fatty," and I didn't think much of that until he stripped off the
bread and several of the pieces were almost entirely fat.  I had never seen
that in a piece of corned beef before.  The other person's reuben had the
same trouble.  Several pieces that were nearly entirely fatty.  This in a
piece of meat that was approximately 2.5 inches by 2.5 inches.  So it
wasn't a little strip.  Then the other problem was a diner at our table of
seven that had ordered fish and chips, his order did not come until nearly
30 minutes after the other six were served.  As it is often polite to wait
until all are served before eating, this would have made everyone's dinner
cold.  Instead, we ate while he waited . . . and waited.  Finally, upon
pointing out to our server the difficulties, it took an inordinate amount
of time to get our checks and then get the checks processed.  The manager
of the hotel came over and made an adjustment of taking off the 18%
gratuity because we were a table of seven, but the time this took to do all
this processing was altogether too long.
I am not by nature a complainer -- have never sent back a meal in my life,
and am typically very generous with my ratings.  However, I felt this
experience overall was just not up to the Hyatt's standards and needed to
be registered.  I look forward to staying there again at some point, and
certainly will give 333 another chance.  But again, thank you for asking.
I am sure this is an aberration.  Take care.
Ed Johnson

2019-10-26 07:06:29] Reply Sent: Click here to respond: Dear Ms. Daily,

Thank you for sharing your feedback with us in the Guest Satisfaction Survey. I want to apologize that your experience during your daughter's special weekend was not as you were hoping for.

We work with brides and grooms to make sure their accommodations are comfortable and we look forward to celebrating with families on their special day. Wedding rooms are blocked and the rates that are set are approved by the bride and groom and signed into contract. Green Bay Packer home games can affect those rates; however, there is still a significant savings plus other benefits for wedding parties. There is also a lot of other times during the year where rates are not as high. 

The standard rate for the weekend of your daughter's wedding was $469.00. The wedding rate that was contracted was $309.00. We also offer complimentary parking, do not require a two-night minimum, and allow wedding guests to cancel their reservations with 48 hour notice. Guests staying in Green Bay during Green Bay Packer home games are required to book a 2-night minimum stay, pre-pay for the reservation in full, and are not allowed to cancel their reservations. They are also charged for parking as well.

I apologize that some of your guests felt that the accommodations that the bride and groom selected did not meet their needs. 

If you would like to discuss anything else about your stay with me, please do not hesitate to reach out. 

Sincerely,

Paul Zagorski
Front Office Manager
Hyatt Regency Green Bay

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;I stayed here on Friday night before I took my dad on the Honor Flight. First making the reservation was extremely difficult, I had to talk to multiple different people, was put on hold for over 30 minutes as nobody seemed to understand what the Flight of Champions was or the discount involved. In fact, I had to call back 2 times to get it resolved and actually get a room booked. Then I called back as instructed to schedule my shuttle for the airport on Saturday morning. I scheduled my dad and myself and was told that only 2 other people were scheduled for the shuttle. I also confirmed this the night we checked in. At check in, I was the 3rd person in line. There was only one person at the desk checking people in on a Friday night. She was nice but then all of the sudden I saw another guy come out of the back room and he didn't help her at all. I had no idea what he was doing but it would have been nice to have another person help with checking in. The next morning my dad and I got up at 3am - got ready and went downstairs to check out at 3:45am. We were putting our items in the car at 3:50 when the shuttle left without us. I went back in to the desk and the person working said "the shuttle was full". I'm like....well I had a reservation that I scheduled 2 weeks ago!! And we were not on it - so who took our spot? The only suggestion was that we get a taxi or an uber that would make us late for getting to the airport. That did not seem like good customer service to me - it was a huge disappointment as we were not the only people who were left behind on a very important day!! I ended up driving myself and another veteran and his son to the airport. This was a terrible way to start the day - and it was the hotel's fault.
Then we are trying to exit and then gate is broke - it took extra time to even get out of the parking lot. A friend of ours had to drive back around, get out and go talk to someone in the hotel to open it. So, no, my experience here was a disaster.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;The hotel staff lacked experience and professionalism. When I initially called to book the room, I was told by a guest support specialist that you were not able to match Hotels.com's room price of $130. After a frustrating 45 minute conversation with your booking department, I hung up and booked through Hotels.com. When we checked in, we were checked under a separate reservation (which was not made by us) through the hotel directly. We were charged again after we had prepaid over a month ago through Hotels.com. Additionally, we were not placed in a room next to the rest of our family as we had requested. When we complained about the double charge and not being next to our family, we were treated very poorly and I was blamed for your mistake. So long story short, we ended up paying $700 for two nights on the other side of the hotel (we were there for my niece's birthday). Hopefully the additional $400 will be refunded, however I have no trust at this point. Also important to note, my sister and father only paid $120 for their rooms (same room that you refused to give me for $130). Very pretty building, but terrible customer service. This was my first stay at a Hyatt. For me, it felt like lipstick on pig. I was very unimpressed with the whole experience.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Room #313 felt very uncomfortable and unsafe. Weird layout, very basement-like darkness (even it is 3rd floor room), no windows and an extra door in addition to the co-joining door that i didn't not have control of locking/unlocking created very unpleasant feeling just in few seconds of entering the room. I don't see many people  wanting to take a risk of staying in the room when you don't know who has a key to get in inside through that extra door while you are asleep. Hotel was sold out, so only after my very strong "encouragement" to the hotel staff of switching up rooms and 15 minutes of waiting in the hallway ( that was recommended by the staff on the phone), I finally went to talk to someone at he frontdesk and was able to get a different room. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Lack of parking spaces was frustrating.  Complementary breakfast, even if only a continental breakfast, would be appreciated.  Buffer breakfast was very good but surprised there was a pricey charge.  Hotel accommodations were excellent!; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column66: At checkout in the app I noted that I had a $4 market charge even though we never visited the market.  The front desk person asked if "I was sure I didn't charge a coffee or something" in kind of a rude way.  If I had charged something to my room, I wouldn't be asking about it. column67: Our handicapped room had a stool for use in the shower.  Upon first morning at the hotel, I noted the front area of the shower entrance was wet even though we hadn't used it. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Hotel was hard to find...not very well lit up or Hyatt displayed. Entry gate too close to the road as well. Check in went well except for the keys did not work so had to go back to front desk. Rey the intern was very good, helpful and cordial. Road was very nice, no issues. Had drinks in the bar, the prices were reasonable but the bar staff was not exceptionally friendly. The TV's are small and none were above the bar which is weird. The bar itself was laid out kind of strange too, no TV's easily accessible from the booths. The place is very spacious, and people at the pool seemed like they were having a good time. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Bathroom in the suite could have been a little better... Seemed to be some poor craftsmanship. Also, I had left my wedding ring in our room and Nicole was great at locating it and calling me to let me know she had found it. However, when I came to the front desk to pick it up there was a new woman behind the computer and when I said "I'm here to pick up my ring" she gave me a concerned look and shook her head slightly as if she knew nothing about it which I didn't expect her to. But the minute I said I was working with Nicole she made a call. For me to have already gone through the steps to find it and be relived and then for her to automatically assume that nothing has been turned in before looking was a little disappointing. I almost went into freak out mode all over again. Something that sentimental should have been handled more professionally from the second employee. But again, Nicole was amazing!; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Charging $7 a night for parking is outrageous. I wouldn't have booked the room had I known I was going to be required to pay that. However, your website doesn't seem to mention it, or maybe that fact is purposefully hidden in some dark and inaccessible corner of the site. That's likely the case as much of what I read on the website was inaccurate and/or out of date. For example, I would have gladly paid extra upon booking my room for breakfast, had I known the breakfast consisted of more than what the website indicated. Basically, what I'm left with is the notion you don't care enough about your customers to provide them with the basic information they need to know to make informed decisions about booking rooms at your hotel. In my opinion, it's hard for business practice to be worse than that.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;When I made the reservation I specifically said that I would have a pet, never once was an additional fee mentioned.  What a shock when I registered that there would be a $100 charge.  Also, while walking from the pool a little after 10 pm, my kids were strictly reminded of the quiet hours.  Mind you, they were not being loud.  Come 12 am, our whole room was woken up with loud shouting, singing and pounding from people running through the halls.  This continued for the next hour or so.  Never did I hear anyone warning them about being quiet.  Will I come back to this hotel, probably not.  Will I recommend it, probably not.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;1- The service at the restaurant was very poor. Long wait both nights with a not full place. One night they had Malbec, the second night the waiter did not even know what a Malbec was.  The quality of the food was good. The Saturday night the kitchen closed without a heads-up and we could not have dessert. 
2- The parking lot was full and we had to park outside of the property. 
3- A portion of the room carpet in my room felt wet the first night. 
4- Front desk employees were nice. 
5- Breakfast was good.; ;The wifi was really poor.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;Had stopped at the front desk to complain about three things. My room #707 had a refrigerator that didn't quite fit in the opening. The wood frame around it was broke. The door was sprung and did not close properly. For me to close it each time, I had to try and slide the unit towards the frame to keep it shut. The clerk told me, we're really sorry about that. Seemed she didn't take my complaint seriously. (Nor the food I had to toss out when I first discovered the problem the first morning of my stay.

Secondly, there were 4-6 inch brown hairs in the wall and ceiling inside the shower/bathtub in my room. 

Third, used the spare blanket that was in the closet container. That to, had some brown hairs on it and also a 3x2 inch pink cool aide type stain on it. 

When I stopped down and complained, the clerk gave me what appeared to be a sad sincere smile, and said, Oh I'm so sorry. Then continued with her other duties. Made me wonder if she understood what I was explaining to her or if that was just the standard response to avoid and problems.

None of my complaints were addressed and I was disappointed on the care of my room and lack of any corrective action. I usually always enjoy staying at the Hyatt and was there for four days, three night attending the WI Chief's of Police Conference. I put up with the problems because I had an expectation that they would be corrected, unfortunately they were not. The conference and facility were great and the evening restaurant/tavern lounge we're excellent.  Just wish I could say the same thing about my room.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column77: This is the third time I have stayed at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay with a large group event. 200+ guests. It is always an exceptional experience. The staff is consistently friendly and they go out of their way to help you, whatever the request. Rooms are spacious, clean and comfortable with many amenities of a suite. Large selection to suit any appetite and dietary need for breakfast. Banquet style dinners were always superb! Restaurant and bar in hotel is wonderful. Great price and value. I would not hesitate to stay there for a solo or family experience. Location is great and convenient to restaurants and shops in downtown Green Bay. Easy access to airport by personal vehicle or hotel shuttle.

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;Overall the hotel was generally clean with a comfortable room. The issue I, along with several other guests who were there attending a conference had was that we were not able to check into our rooms at 3:00pm like your policy states. We were not able to check in until 5:30 pm. The reason that was given was because they hadn't been cleaned yet. It was apparent to me that since there was a professional football team staying in the hotel with us that their rooms got priority in being cleaned. Not sure why this had to happen. Management obviously knew that the hotel was booked with a football team along with our conference attendees why didn't they bring in extra cleaning personnel? 

The second issue I had was when on Tuesday evening i went down to the bar with several of my fellow conference attendees and waited for over ten minutes to get a drink. There were three bartenders on the bar was maybe half full and we were never even acknowledged. We eventually went to a different establishment to get served. Very disappointed in this Hyatt's service.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column77:
This is my third time staying at this property, and the staff has always been helpful and courteous and the rooms wonderful. The food at the breakfast buffet is tasty, with a nice variety, and the hotel bar is congenial, well-stocked and also has local beers.

Only complaints would be that the elevators are slow, and the maid service on Saturday wasn't as good as during the weekdays.

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;When I checked in I was never told to validate my parking ticket. My reservation was suppose to be points and somehow I was charged. I found this out when I noticed a charge on my credit card. I wen to the front desk to get this taken care of and after wasting 30 minutes was told they could t help me a that I needed to call “World of Hyatt”.
I had just spent the entire day in the hospital for my son so I called the next morning. I called World if Hyatt, the next morning and they told me to have the hotel call them to issue rewards for my stay.
That was another 15 minutes. I then called one of the hotel managers to help me with this. She wasn’t very friendly but did however take care of the point vs charge for my stay.
From a housekeeping stand; 
The paper towels in my room were nasty. Stained with something Grosse. I had asked the front desk the first time I saw them but was ignored. They didn’t take care of this until I had to complain twice. This is unacceptable!
I also asked the front desk to see if house keeping could clean my balcony ( it had a ton of spider webs and spiders). Their response was “Oh the balconies are not to be stood on. I mean nothing has happened yet but you shouldn’t use it”
My response: 
This should have been mentioned when I made the reservation or at least at check in.
I am so disappointed in Hyatt, Green Bay!; ;Please see my notes from earlier.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

On the second day, I was left with no floor mat nor any washcloths.  Also on the second day, I tried to request of few of their advertised complimentary items and was told they were out of 2 of the items I requested.  Not a huge deal but if you advertise it in the room, you should make sure you are stocked on everything. 
 
Finally, they are not properly staffed for busy check-in or check-out times.  Each time, there was only one person who could help any of us.  A gentleman wearing a manager name tag was just standing at a work station unable to help anyone needing to check out.  What?  Why is he a manager if he cannot check people out and instead stands there as we are left to stand in line waiting for the one lady who apparently could check people out. column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;The food service the 2 mornings seemed a bit confusing - we did not have a definite server and asked a couple of times for refill on coffee and no one helped.  
I was actually a bit disappointed in our stay this time - it seems as if Hyatt employees though very professional are losing their friendliness and welcoming ways.  It feels like a corporation when you enter the doors.  I actually was a bit intimidated to ask a couple of questions.
This is an example that we witnessed during our stay - there was a young family - the father broke his foot the day before and was walking with crutches.  He had a toddler holding on to one of the crutches with him - the mother was pushing a stroller trying to get another toddler to hold on to the side and she was holding an infant.  No one on the Hyatt Staff asked them if they needed help to their car or even looked their way as the toddler was crying.  We helped them maneuver the parking lot.  The next morning when they were down at breakfast my husband and I helped the mom with her 3 children at the buffet.  When we were checking out we had to tell the front desk to please help them when there would be checking out.  I was really disappointed that your staff is very professional - almost to intimidation - that they have lost kindness.
On the other hand - I did have a good experience making the reservation with Emma and also adding another evening on with Katie.  Both were very helpful.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Had ADA King room with roll in shower.  Need to replace the permanent toilet bar on outside with a wall mount lift up and down unit.  Some wheelchair people need to transfer onto the toilet from the side. The entry door should operate with automatic wall buttons.  Location of ADA rooms should be on ground floor or floor with access to sky walk so wheelchair bound people can get out of building in case of fire and elevators cannot be used. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Whenever my husband and I come to Green Bay we always stay at the Hyatt on Main. Every room is a suite with a bar and lounge area right as you walk in and the bedroom is at the back which is great because your beds are not right up against the door where there will be walking traffic going by the door. The room is very comfortable and the buffet breakfast held in the 1st floor commons area is wonderful. They offer Steel Cut Oatmeal, Scrambled Eggs, bacon, muffins, fresh fruit, toast, bagels and fresh pastries. On the weekends there is an omelette station & you are able to go back for seconds if you so desire. There is a wonderful pool and hot tub just off this main area on 1st floor and they are both wonderful. The water in the pool isn't too cold like in many pools and there is ample room to swim. In addition there is a PUB in the 1st floor lobby area that serves lunch and dinner as well as having a bar. Their food is very good. I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone as it is a comfortable stay and the people that work there are very accommodating.; ;Again I highly recommend staying at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay on Main St. It is definitely worth it!; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

In addition there is a PUB in the 1st floor lobby area that serves lunch and dinner as well as having a bar. Their food is very good. I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone as it is a comfortable stay and the people that work there are very accommodating.
column66: Whenever my husband or myself encountered staff everyone was always friendly and asking if there was anything else they could do for you. The staff at this hotel want to make everyone feel like they are important.
column67: I found our room to be very clean and the hotel in general also very clean. With the size of this hotel (8 floors) one usually sees carts outside of rooms when they are being cleaned as it takes a lot of time to clean all of these rooms and the cleaning staff do an excellent job of it.
column68: Since I spoke about the Breakfast Buffet I will now concentrate more on the PUB restaurant/bar that is located on the 1st floor. My husband and i have stayed at this hotel many times over the past 10+ years and we have always found good food at the Pub. This time around we had the Chicken Wraps, and one of the salads with grilled Salmon on top. Both were excellent. Staff is very accommodating and work hard to make sure you are getting what you ordered and that you are satisfied with it.
column69: Again I highly recommend staying at the Hyatt Regency Green Bay on Main St. It is definitely worth it!

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;My low marks are a result of our car getting hit in the parking lot (rented mini van).  Also, the breakfast was a disaster from basically no food due to a insurance convention at which all of the people seemed to be overeating...so I think it was impossible for the Hyatt to keep up with the demand.  Nonetheless, when our family tried to eat, there was not alot of food left and the food was cold. The parking lot accident was a result of the night security guard telling us to park in an end slot...which wasnt actually a parking space...but he directed us to that spot.  In all fairness, though, whomever hit our car was totally at fault.  Also, it was a hit and run.  No note left. Morning security guard was excellent as were the GB Police when we filed the report.; ;comments noted on first page of survey; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;I called the morning I was checking in to double check the pricing and everything was fine. At check in hours later I was told they over booked the type of room I had reserved. I’m still unsure of why someone else got that room and I did not as I work in the hospitality industry myself. I was merely satisfied with the money taken off, and ridiculous parking fees waived, (I mean seriously who charges people who are staying at their hotel to park?) and the breakfast buffet was comped as well. But still have never understood overbooking a room style, staff should know hotel and computer operating systems for Hyatt cooperation should really be top notch. 

To the guest room. We stayed in a double queen suite and was mildly clean, living area tables were dusty and comforter for couch bed had stains on it. In the fridge was a corona in the freezer from what I would guess to be the guest before us. Every mirror was foggy, streaky, or had toothpaste spit on the bottom. They obviously did not vacuum. 4 bath towels, 2 hand towels, and 1 wash cloth was the towel amenities in our guest room. Shower curtain had orange stain on it. Toilet bowl was dirty as well. 
Restaurant was fun! Bartender was nice and had good drinks and the food was amazing tasting and great portions. Servers were a little inexperienced. But nice. 
My family also loved the oversized toys, games of checkers, connect 4, uno. And my family had a good time. We loved the window elevator.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;I travel often and stay at Hampton Inn.  My boys and I took this vacation together and decided to try the Hyatt in Green Bay since others in the area were sold out or too expensive due to the Oskosh Air Show.  One thing that instantly turns me off to a hotel is hair - not mine since I am bald and just walked into the room.  Black hair on one of the beds.  I washed my face and dried off with a bath towel and got a long brown hair on my face from the towel.  Also, a few pieces of black hair in the tub at arrival. I looked up and saw a few long hairs stuck to the bathroom ceiling where it had been wiped down.  Sorry to say, but this is enough for me to not stay at the Hyatt again.  One other thing––charged $7 a night for parking in the front lot.  The third night there were no spaces and was told to park in the parking garage that was close...since "they didn't charge overnight".  Wondering if there was no charge, why the Hyatt charged me $7 for not parking in their lot?; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

; ; ; ; ; ;From checking in on Day 1 and our entire 12 day stay Noely was the utmost professional and provided superior Customer Service. column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;The hotel itself was fine. The front desk staff was exceptional, very helpful and knowledgeable. 
The restaurant manager on the other hand.... 
He knew we had seated ourselves and seemingly was standing around with the bar staff. Our waitress was clearly new, she came over apologizing about our wait (we had to get our own menus from the bar). She took our drink order answered our questions, and then retuned with our drinks to take our food order. After a 30-40 minute wait in a not busy restaurant we got our food. After we got our food one of the sides was wrong. The waitress did not check on us for awhile, so we approached the bar to find out the person standing behind the bar, was the manager. We let him know that there was an issue with the order. Our waitress came out and told us it would be a few minutes until our order was out.... another 20 minutes go by. No manager has checked on us, and we still don’t have our side of sweet potato fries. We approached the bar to inquire, and let them know at this point we shouldn’t be paying for the sandwich this was ridiculously slow service. 
Once we got the food and the bill, the manager again was no where to be found. After 20 minutes of waiting to find the manger who was “in a different department”, I went to the front desk to have him paged. We tried explaining to him the ridiculousness of this whole situation. He then decided he should blame his wait staff for not relaying the message that the sandwich would be free to us. 
We ended up arguing to have the full bill taken care of. Had this manager come out to the table apologized for the mistake, checked on us or our food, there would have been no issue. Mistakes happen. But to then blame it on the wait staff for not relaying his message. That was absurd. There was no apology no customer service from the manager just blame placed on his staff. Unacceptable. That put a bitterness on our entire stay. The breakfast was excellent and the service from the staff was great.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column77: I’m going to start by saying that we were here for a wedding and thus were able to get the room for a slightly lower rate. Because we only paid around $130 a night I gave it 3 stars. If I had paid more it would have been 2. Our room smelled pleasant and was spacious. (Our friends however had a much smaller room that was the “same” as ours.) Upon arrival there were visible pieces of dirt on the couch—as if someone put their feet up and the dirt fell off of their shoes. When you sat on the couch you could see that no one had vacuumed the crease between the a attached cushion and the actual couch—there were visible crumbs and hair. There was a door separating the sitting area and bed area, which was nice. The bathroom had dirty/stained grout, badly repaired leaks, and no toilet paper or Kleenex. I expect a hotel bathroom to be cleaner and nicer than my bathroom because it should be getting cleaned every other day or so, but this just did not feel that way. The towels and bed linens were not the quality I would expect from a Hyatt, but they weren’t awful. The “comforter” was a thin, deflated, down comforter covered with a plain white sheet. But it was clean. The bed was not comfortable for me or my spouse. I did appreciate the wet bar with fridge and microwave. I also liked that it came with a separate makeup mirror that you could move to a table and sit to do your makeup. Overall it was okay. We got what we paid for.

column68: almost all food I ate was buffet style, except for final banquet.  food amounts were usually adequate, but almost always lukewarm or cold instead of hot.  one example of this was the mac and cheese on the Thursday buffet dinner.  the Wednesday buffet dinner had chicken tenders which were tough and dry, but the rest of the food was good.  the breakfast buffet was good, but ran out of orange juice and coffee.
column69: overall my experience was good

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;The things that were annoying include the slow elevator and not have an access door to the ground floor from the staircase.  There probably are "security" reasons, however, I wanted to use the stairs to get to the ground floor and that wasn't an option.

I'd like to thank the maintenance crew for repairing the hot tub in such a short time.  Friday night the hot tub water was lowering quickly and all of a sudden the water was splashing everywhere.  Mainenance was there quickly and fixed it instead of closing it (as other hotels would have done).  I was able to enjoy the hot tub once again on Saturday morning, prior to checkout. 

It was awesome to be able to check into my room at 12:30 rather than 3:00.  This greatly helped me organize the day since I had tasks to be part of all afternoon and evening with our convention that was there.  

I totally enjoyed all of the food for breakfast and for our evening meal.  In my opinion, the food was prepared wonderfully and served hot enough to enjoy.  The buffet table on Wednesday and Thursday were kept stocked that even those of us that couldn't get there until way after it opened were able to have hot fresh food.  Saturday's banquet was great.  I even enjoyed the vegetables.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column67: My room was wonderful and I didn't hear any hallway noise or noise from above or next door.  The bed was comfortable.  It took awhile for my shower to get warm water, but that was fine.  I also really like the bar soap for the shower.
column68: I really enjoyed all of the food.  The brats were done a little more than I personally like, but they were not dried out.  the steak was perfect.  I loved the fish and the pork with gravy.  I even think the salt level was low enough that I could eat more of.  I am on a salt restriction most of the time.  Thank you to the chef and kitchen staff for great food.
column77: All amenities were in great working order -- pool, hot tub, steam room, sauna.  Breakfast was able to be served fast and hot to get the day off to a good start.  Staff friendly and helpful.  Room was quiet and very comfortable.

Only issue was figuring out the location. Had to use google maps to find our way from the hotel to the mall, considering it was in a part of Green Bay that I’m not used to going to.

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;1)Kristin was wonderful and so thoughtful. She really set the tone for a great stay. 
2)Toilet clogged quickly for some reason. Staff fixed it quickly though and it worked fine all weekend. 
3)Breakfast was good overall, sausages under done or not browned, pastries very delightful. Nice selection of beverage choices. Staff was excellent!
After reviewing my statements above I must say bravo and thank you for hiring wonderful people, they make all the difference.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Check in was super simple and every person on staff that we encountered with weekend was so kind and genuine and lovely. My only complaints are that there are not enough pictures of the the rooms online so you can judge what works for you before you get there, (as of today there is only one picture of the room type I booked on the website and it only shows half of the suite), it would help greatly if you included room layouts in the room photos so guests could see exactly what they are getting and make sure it is right for them. My other complaint was the food in the bar was incredibly pricey for very small portions, I believe I paid between $12-$15 for 3 chicken strips and some fries and that didn't even include a dipping sauce option.The food also took a very long time to come out but I do understand that that was probably because the kitchen was very busy with all the convention goers that were there that weekend. All in all I had a good stay, but a few tweaks could make a huge difference for next time.; ;I don't think it really made any difference.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

My only complaints are that there are not enough pictures of the the rooms online so you can judge what works for you before you get there, (as of today there is only one picture of the room type I booked on the website and it only shows half of the suite), it would help greatly if you included room layouts in the room photos so guests could see exactly what they are getting and make sure it is right for them. My other complaint was the food in the bar was incredibly pricey for very small portions, I believe I paid between $12-$15 for 3 chicken strips and some fries and that didn't even include a dipping sauce option.The food also took a very long time to come out but I do understand that that was probably because the kitchen was very busy with all the convention goers that were there that weekend. All in all I had a good stay, but a few tweaks could make a huge difference for next time.
column66: Everyone was absolutely fantastic! And the front desk and house keeping were super helpful in getting my lost item back to me.
column67: My guest room was great, it was weird that there were no bags in the garbage but I understand that is probably done to cut down on plastic waste with I appreciate. My only complaint about the room is not being able to see a layout or even more than one photo before hand. My major complaint would be the elevators, they are in desperate need of an update. The convention I was a part of at the hotel brought in 3400 people and while I know some didn't stay at the hotel I know many did, and with 8 floors and so many people needing to go up and down all the time the wait time got crazy at some points.
column68: We had lunch at about 11:30am on Friday July 12th in the pub. My chicken strips were good but $12-$15 for 3 strips and some fries was a little ridiculous. One of the other people at my table had the mac and cheese and was less than impressed, again it was expensive, the portion was small, and the sauce was an off texture. The other 2 at my table enjoyed their pulled pork quesadilla and burger, but again the price compared to the portions left much to be desired. We didn't send back the mac and cheese because we had waited so long for the food to come out the in the first place (a believe 30-45min) that we would have missed the start of our event if we waited again. Our waitress was great but we will probably not be returning again. We did also have the breakfast buffet 2 of the mornings of our stay and it was great, though the french toast on Sunday was very overcooked.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;This was my third time staying at the Hyatt Regency in Green Bay.  I usually visit the Green Bay area 1-3 times a year.  Every other experience has been wonderful.  This last experience makes it unlikely that I will return.  The room I stayed in was not clean.  The bathroom fan had mold surrounding it, and there was mold around the toilet.  There were light red stains on one of the beds comforters and black curly hairs on one of the beds pillows.  Seeing the state of the room we went to the front desk and requested another room.  We were told that someone could go and clean the room because there were no other rooms in the hotel for us to switch to.  When we said we would just like a refund and would be leaving a room was then available.  The second room was fine and the rest of the stay was fine.  However having the first room in such rough condition, and having to go and plea for another room or leave put a damper on the evening. I also feel like it is crazy to charge $7 for parking when there is not an event going on.  The parking gate to leave was also up the entire time so anyone would have been able to come and go making the $7 charge pointless.  We did receive a coupon for a free item for in the Hyatt Marketplace and were able to switch rooms.  I am cautious/unlikely to return though based on how things went during my last visit.; ;The staff who checked me in were wonderful and thanked me for being a repeat visitor.  The lobby is beautiful and kept very clean.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;My fiancé and I booked the Hyatt in Green Bay, WI, because we had previously stayed at a Hyatt in Chicago, IL-- and loved it. We are very displeased with our stay in at the Hyatt, in WI, and will not be returning. 
Here are a few things, which have steered our stay to other locations moving forward.
1. The room was not clean. We arrived and paid for early check in-- yet got put in a room that had dust all over the place.
2. The tv had a burn mark. 
3. The carpet had a wrinkle in it, between the sliding door and bed, causing me to trip in the middle of the night. 
4. Went to look in the brochure to find the floor in which the laundry room was, and the brochure appeared to be half eaten by an animal-- therefore we had to call the lobby for them to tell us, what we should have been able to know without calling. That's the whole point of a brochure in a guest room. Very inconvenient. 
5. The view that we had was horrendous. Opening our curtains, to find we had a beautiful view of the AC units. 
6. We paid extra for the morning breakfast. Upon arrival, there was no host. We asked a server and she said "seat yourself, and someone will come get your drinks." We did just that. And 10 minutes went by. We had to get up not just once, but twice to get our drinks. That is terrible service and very  unacceptable. 

Like stated above, we will not be returning to the Hyatt Hotels. The many inconveniences and awful service in the dining area, have made up our mind, that we will in fact take our money elsewhere and stay where we feel we are appreciated.

Thank you,

Thank you so much for taking the time to respond to our guest satisfaction survey, and for your valuable feedback. I sincerely apologize for the issues experienced in our parking lot; please know that we do not allow any boats or trailers in our front lot in consideration of our guests, and the vehicle that illegally parked was appropriately ticketed. However, if a guest needs to utilize overflow parking, located in the Main Street Parking Ramp, we are more than happy to remove the $7 nightly parking fee, as that fee is only applicable to guests who are parked in our lot overnight. However, I do hope the rest of your stay was enjoyable, and we hope to see you again soon!

If you have any further concerns, or if I can be of any assistance, please feel free to contact me directly.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Our room was booked with the breakfast buffet.  When checking out I reminded the staff that I ate breakfast and she assured me it would not hit my bill as an additional charge.  When I received the online bill there was a $42 charge for breakfast.  So I called the front desk to remind them to remove and they said they would immediately and send me an updated e-mail.  I waited about 8 hours and still did not receive the e-mail so I called again.   This time the person was very helpful but she did say the prior person did not remove as she said she would.  I should not have to chase down overcharges on my vacation when I booked the room with breakfast.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Our room was intended to have a "mini fridge" in it, however, the mini-fridge was marked "cooler" instead and it was set in to a cabinet in such a way that it was impossible to easily shut the door.  The door was accidentally left open due to the cabinet (it looked shut), which led to the items in there spoiling.  Additionally, we checked in with a "bed and breakfast rate" that included the breakfast buffet.  I had to ask how we were to do that, and the front desk person was unsure.  We were also offered a "quiet" room when we checked in online.  The room we had most certainly was not quiet as my son (who was on the pull-out couch) was kept awake by children running up and down the hallway the first night we were there.; ;We were not told until check-in that parking would be $7/day.  While I do see it on the website now - having looked for it - it was not made clear when making the reservation - it does not appear anywhere on the reservation process and summary of billing.  Also, having to get our parking ticket validated for each and every in & out (and keep track of it) was more than a little bit of a hassle, considering we were sight-seeing.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column68: While the buffet was a nice location, quite frankly, I'm shocked that had we not booked the "bed and breakfast rate" that we would have been charged $12.50 per person for not much more that we have had for "free continental breakfasts" at other locations.
column69: We were not told until check-in that parking would be $7/day.  While I do see it on the website now - having looked for it - it was not made clear when making the reservation - it does not appear anywhere on the reservation process and summary of billing.  Also, having to get our parking ticket validated for each and every in & out (and keep track of it) was more than a little bit of a hassle, considering we were sight-seeing.

column77:
Took the family to Green Bay for a summer trip.  Room and hotel was very clean.  Parking was just fine.
Everything was very clean and worked good.  The kids had fun in the pool and everyone liked the design of the hotel and atomsphere.  
The breakfast was a little pricey, but it had great quality product. Maybe they could look into a little  lower price for kids so you don't have to pay so much just for a family breakfast.

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;The room and bathroom were overall clean, but the bathroom trash can was not emptied from the last stay. Room service took over an hour and came as I was walking out of the door to check out, A part of my order was eggs and bacon and I received eggs and hash browns and they were just thrown together in box mixed. This is the second stay that we have had issues with room service. The last time we were here we also got none of our requests met, we really needed towels and coffee and didn’t get them. Food service wasn’t even picking up that trip, I kept getting routed to front desk, took 30 minutes to place an order with someone. We really like this place and will keep coming back but really hope we don’t continue having these issues.; ;Overall very good, will stay here in future; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column68:

column77: The rooms include a seating area, breakfast bar with cooler and microwave, a smaller, but functional bathroom. And an entirely separate room with a bed, closet, dresser, and balcony. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Never staying there again. They don’t have enough parking for all the hotel guests if there’s a wedding or convention. Check in is at 3 but when I arrived at 5:15 with all my luggage and 4 kids, my room wasn’t ready and I had to wait in the lobby until my room was clean. The knob was falling off my bathroom door. When I made the reservation and when I checked in I requested a crib but a request was never made. I had to call the front desk again from the room and request a crib for a third time before I got one. I forgot something in the pool area and called the hotel the next day to see if it was in lost and found, I was on hold for 15 mins and never got an answer and finally hung up because I was on my way into work and couldn’t wait any longer.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;1. I have a handicapped permit; no spots were available. No apologies for inadequate handicapped spaces, only a lecture and advise to go to public parking. Again, no apology for requiring me to walk further. 2. On checking in, having purchased an upgrade that included breakfast, I received not "Welcome," nor any info about how to redeem the breakfasts. When I returned to inquire, rather than giving me the info directly, I was asked for my room number so they could verify my eligibility. 3. When I arrived, all parking lot gates were open. When I tried to leave, the gate was closed. Again I went to registration. "Didn't you have your ticket stamped?" she asked. "What ticket?" I asked. Then I was told there was a button I could push. I made a complaint about the generally bad service. I got no apology but a lecture on why "things were as they were." 4. Our convention is booked for there again next year. I hope that the front desk personnel are all required to take a course is simple hospitality. Perhaps they could learn something from Hampton Inns where I've never had a negative experience of hundreds of stays.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

I wanted to enjoy a nice summer evening after a day at the conference and found out that others had taken a nice walk along the river that evening. column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;The room smelled damp and musty which could be because it was above the pool. I was using points and was initially given a room on the 2nd floor overlooking the room and AC units. I requested a different room with a view and was given a 2nd floor room over looking a busy street. Was I given poor locations due to my using points? The parking lot was full both nights causing me to have to park across the street in a public lot, and then go to the front desk and get my parking ticket for the Hyatt lot cancelled. I was prepared for this problem, as it was noted in many Trip Advisor comments. However, the front desk never made mention of what to do for alternate parking arrangements if the lot is full. Complementary valet should be offered on nights with high occupancy or events (such as a wedding which was occurring when I was there).; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

Thank you for taking the time to respond to our guest satisfaction survey, and for your valuable feedback. I apologize that you didn't enjoy your stay with us. We did attempt to extend pool hours for the baseball teams, but due to designated adult swim hours, we did need to clear the pool at the request of other guests. We try our best to create a welcoming and tranquil environment for all guests regardless of what brings them to our hotel, which does include quiet hours, though conversely we do proudly offer games for families during the day on weekends, as well as our pool area every day from 5 AM-10 PM for anyone under 18. However, we do hope that if you find yourself in the Green Bay area again, that we will have the opportunity to serve you as our guest again.

There were patrons at 5 tables and 2 people serving. The service was terrible. No one around for extended periods. Coffee was barely warm. I finally flagged down my waitress who proceeded to pour me another coffee, but it was now essentially cold out of the coffee pot. My omelette was mediocre, and the hash-browns were so over-salted with seasoning salt that they were essentially inedible. I waited for my waitress to come back... and waited... and... finally gave up and walked to the front desk who credited me the meal. I paid for breakfast with the room charge, but never ate there again. Rotten experience.

I had dinner at the bar twice and it was a pleasant experience both times.

Also, the thermostat in the room - setting it at 70 degrees left the room at about 64.  I turned it up to 74 and the room warmed up to the high 60s. After setting it to about 80 the room warmed up to 70.

column64:
; ; ; ; ; ;Food for the buffet was just barely warm except for the eggs were always hot. All breads were dry like they had been frozen to long. For $32 and a $10 cash tip I probably wouldn't spend that type of money on the buffet again. I did bring this to the attention of the staff somebody came out to rectify it. However by this time we were finishing up our plates and had to leave. on the second day the food temperatures were the same. On the third day we eat elsewhere.

As advertised on your website and in the years past when I stayed at your property a mini fridge  was provided. However this time the temperature was 45 to 47 degrees. A labeled stated "this is cooler" on the outside of the mini refrigerator. This is very alarming to me. I rented at this property because of the 2 room and I needed the use of a refrigerator. I did share my concerns with the front desk and they offered to bring me some ice packs. If all I wanted was a cooler I could have brought my own cooler from home and filled it with ice. They had no others to switch with nor any other rooms to switch so I was just stuck with a cooler in my room. Very alarming and we did not eat the food that was stored in the refrigerator. I was concerned of the potential health concerns. I'm aware frigerator according to the State regulations need to be 36 to 38 degrees.

The air conditioner never became any cooler than 71 degrees. Apparently there was something wrong with the air-conditioning. They did however provide me with a fan. It's unfortunate we had multiple rooms in use but only one fan could be provided.

In the past we have had great experiences at your property and that's why we continue to rebook. Perhaps these were just isolated issues.

I would like to make a note that the staff was absolutely outstanding. I did voice all of my concerns and each time.  They were sincerely apologetic and tried to accommodate and rectify the situations. I understand that there's only so much they could do.

Thank You,

Dan and Sherry Reno; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;Very dissatisfied with the parking!  When I checked in on May 15 around 5pm, there were no open parking slots in the Hyatt surface parking lot.  Front desk told me that overflow parking was in the city parking ramp around the corner.  I asked if the procedure for validating the parking receipt for the surface lot was the same for the overflow parking.  The woman working the front desk told me yes.  I checked out on May 17 and was told that the receipt from the overflow parking ramp could NOT be validated!  The $13.60 charge for parking was very disappointing!; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;

column77: They have a small surface lot for hotel guests, where you get a ticket upon entry.  As a hotel guest you get it validated at the front desk and enter this ticket upon exit.  The problem is that the lot is small and when full, they send you across the street to the city parking ramp where evidently the parking ticket is not validated by Hyatt!  I was told at check-in that the city parking ramp ticket would be validated!  The other problem is, even though the Hyatt surface lot is full, there is no notification upon entering that the lot is full, so you end up getting a ticket and then to get out of the lot to find additional parking, you have to go inside the hotel to get your ticket validated!  This is not Chicago!  I do not want to be hassled with parking at a medicore facility and downtown like this!

column64: ; ; ; ; ; ;the light in my room under the side table by the bed was frustrating. Disliked it. We went tot he on site restaurant 2 times and both times we terrible. The first time the spoon I got was completely filthy- dried on food on it that was super obvious- not a small speck- a large amount. The chili I ordered that came with the dirty spoon was cold- not just not super hot but COLD. How can that even happen? We didnt have a lot of time on our break so sent it back and just had the other thing I ordered. Then when my bill came I was still charged for the chili I sent back?! I asked her to remove it and she did but not only should she have removed it without asking at that point, someone should have maybe come to the table to appologise or offer a free soda or something? It was like they didnt even care. The second experience was for breakfast- food was not warm (eggs, sausages or hashbrowns) all of us were sorry we stayed in for breakfast- would have been worth the drive to get a good breakfast. Many dished were not even half full. Kind of dried out- and we were mid way through the monring not at the very end or anything? Lastly the parking was a huge problem- everytime we had to leave the hotel we couldnt park in the lot anymore. Had to park blocks away in the rain. Over all not a good experience.; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ; ;
